The paper discusses formal methods, specification, and verification of real-time systems, which are topics commonly found in the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of timed automata and the focus on time intervals also suggest a connection to the sub-category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). However, since the paper does not explicitly mention this sub-category, it is ranked lower in likelihood.
